      "name": "Visa Number Selector / Default",
      "context": "Visa Number Selector / Default — Inline selector used ONLY in the Visa / Add form (NOT the dashboard switcher). Lets the user pick which visa number they are adding: 1st, 2nd, or 3rd WHV 417. Shows 3 card-style options side by side. Each card has a colored ordinal badge (1st=$--visa-1st-color green, 2nd=$--visa-2nd-color blue, 3rd=$--visa-3rd-color amber) with white text, and a 'WHV 417' label below in muted color. Cards have neutral background and border — no selected state in this default variant. In React: a controlled radio-group. On select, highlights the chosen option (see nqZxc for 1st-selected state). The selected value determines which ordinal badge color is used in blockedRanges for other visas in the calendar.",
