    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "KKpmy",
      "x": 4445,
      "y": 5400,
      "name": "Visa Date Picker / Calendar / Blocked Range",
      "context": "Visa Date Picker / Calendar / Blocked Range — Shows a month where all dates are blocked by an existing visa. Example: January 2025 fully covered by the 1st WHV (arrival Jan 1 2025). Blocked days: muted gray text (#9ca3af), no background fill on cells, a small solid colored underline bar (3px, rounded, 16px wide) placed BELOW each day number — NOT as a background overlay. The bar color matches the visa ordinal: 1st=$--visa-1st-color (#10b981 green), 2nd=$--visa-2nd-color (#3b82f6 blue), 3rd=$--visa-3rd-color (#f59e0b amber). Colors are stored as design variables (not hardcoded). A legend below the grid shows which visa blocks which range: colored bar swatch + 'Nth WHV 417 — D Mon to D Mon YYYY'. Info hint: 'Your arrival date must be outside existing visa periods'. In React: receives a blockedRanges prop — Array<{ start: Date, end: Date, visaOrdinal: 1|2|3 }>. Each range renders using $--visa-Nth-color. Non-blocked days are fully interactive. The component is powered by shadcn/ui Calendar (DayPicker). Blocked dates use the disabled modifier + custom DayContent to inject the underline bar.",
